The **Time Elemental** is a [defunct](/wiki/Defunct_features_\(SpliceHack\) "Defunct features (SpliceHack)") monster in [SpliceHack](/wiki/SpliceHack "SpliceHack"). It was the [quest nemesis](/wiki/Quest_nemesis "Quest nemesis") of the defunct [dancer](/wiki/Dancer "Dancer") role. Defeating the Time Elemental yielded the **spellstrike slide** [technique](/wiki/Technique "Technique").

Time Elemental

From NetHackWiki
Jump to navigation Jump to search
E Time Elemental
Difficulty 27
Attacks Weapon 4d6 slowing, Weapon 4d6 slowing, Claw 1d6 sonic, Claw 1d6 psychic, Claw 1d6 fire, Claw 1d6 cold
E Time Elemental
Difficulty 27
Attacks

Weapon 4d6 slowing, Weapon 4d6 slowing, Claw 1d6 sonic, Claw 1d6 psychic, Claw 1d6 fire, Claw 1d6 cold

Base level 18
Base experience 735
Speed 16
Base AC 2
Base MR 30
Alignment 0 (neutral)
Frequency (by normal means) Unique
Genocidable No
Weight 2500
Nutritional value 0
Size Gigantic
Resistances poison,petrification,fire,cold,sonic
Resistances conveyed None

The Time Elemental:

  • can fly.
  • can phase through walls.
  • does not breathe.
  • has no eyes.
  • has no head.
  • does not have a solid form.
  • does not eat. (*)
  • is neither male nor female.
  • is normally generated hostile.
  • is nasty.
  • is strong.
  • wants your quest artifact.
  • never leaves a corpse.

The Time Elemental is a defunct monster in SpliceHack. It was the quest nemesis of the defunct dancer role. Defeating the Time Elemental yielded the spellstrike slide technique.
